{
  "texts": [
    "In the EU, they have the regulatory classification of at least moderate risk in-vitro diagnostic devices/medical devices [44] [45] [46].",
    "In the US, they are classified as non-medical devices if non-urgent advice is delivered with: (i) alternatives; (ii) a basis; (iii) evidence; (iv) no processing of image or signal data; (v) approaches for the prevention of automation bias 47.",
    "Large language model (LLM)based CDS approaches have recently been proposed including in the area of oncology [48] [49] [50], which show impressive but variable performance 51, 52.",
    "Some LLM-based approaches are being built into clinical charting systems 53, 54.",
    "LLM-based chatbots, which claim to provide medical advice to patients, are also being made available on the EU market in a manner that is likely illegal (29)."
  ]
}